##рЯМН GeoAssist вАФ AI-Powered Geo Data Cleaning Framework on Databricks


> **A reusable, config-driven framework that uses an LLM to detect and correct typos in geographic fields вАФ city, state, country вАФ directly inside Databricks. No domain expert required.**


---
 
## The Problem
 
Every data engineer has seen this in raw data:
 
| Raw (dirty) | Correct |
|---|---|
| `Mumbay` | `Mumbai` |
| `Chenai` | `Chennai` |
| `New Yrok` | `New York` |
| `Untied Kingdom` | `United Kingdom` |
| `Germaany` | `Germany` |
 
These typos break downstream joins, corrupt dashboards, and usually require a domain expert or hundreds of regex rules to fix. This framework replaces all of that with a single LLM-backed Spark UDF.
 
---
 
##  What GeoAssist Does
 
- Reads raw geo data from a **Unity Catalog Volume** (no data movement needed)
- Uses **LLaMA 3.3 70B** via the Databricks Foundation Models API to validate each value
- Returns a **confidence score + correction** for every row
- Routes rows into **3 Silver tables** based on confidence
- Publishes a final **Gold geo master table** ready for downstream joins
- Works on **any dataset** вАФ just change the column names in the config
---

## рЯУВ Project Structure
 
```
GeoAssist/
вФЬвФАвФА validator.ipynb          # AI core вАФ LLM prompts, GeoValidator class, smoke test
вФЬвФАвФА 01_bronze.ipynb          # Ingest raw files + run AI validati
```

 
## рЯЧВпЄП Datasets Used
 
| File | Source | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `airports.dat.txt` | [OpenFlights](https://openflights.org/data.html) | Raw dirty geo data (14,000+ airports) |
| `cities500.txt` | [GeoNames](https://download.geonames.org/export/dump/) | Clean reference data for LLM context |
 
Both files are stored in a **Unity Catalog Volume** at:
```
/Volumes/geo_assist/raw/geo_assist/
```


To adapt this to **your own dataset**: change `AIRPORTS_FILE` to your file path and update `TARGET_COLUMNS` to match your column names. That's it.
